snippet.textDisplay:
Not gonna lie, I don't see the Discord marketplace being all too successful.
Yeah it's convenient*, but they have to complete with Steam. They'd have to compete against their summer sales, flash sales, and the fact that people already have massive libraries on Steam. What unique features does Discord's marketplace have over Steam? Short of stripping away the overlay on non-discord platform release games, which would in turn increase the likelihood of people using BetterDiscord or some other third party client that still has it/refusing to update, they can't really offer too much.

*Really the only convenient feature is being able to start any game from Discord. Even then, assuming you're using a Steam release, just double click the icon and it should just work.
